title: Anne of the Island
creator: Lucy Maud Montgomery
description: LibriVox recording of Anne of the Island by Lucy Maud Montgomery. Read by Karen Savage. Anne is off to Redmond College! She will spend the next three years living and learning, making new friends, and deepening old friendships. For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobook; anne; montgomery
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
This reading is, as good as any previous Karen Savage work. However, there are some chapters where the recording sounds a little strange. Too much echo and not a crisp sound. It seems like a problem with the microphone.

Karen Savage works is excellent, though.

Third book in the Anne of Green Gables series, just as good as the first two, and again read by the great Karin Savage!

Re the previous comment - the sound in one chapter only was a little off, but nothing serious.
